   domain. As a result of progressing in two separate disciplines, the
   literature on marketing strategy and the upper echelons is fragmented
   and disjointed. We develop an organizing framework to review extant
   research and assess and synthesize the knowledge in the upper echelons
   marketing strategy domain. Our review covers the 14 most influential
   marketing and management journals from 1984 through February, 2020.
