   products. A large-scale field study and four experiments demonstrate
   that weather affects product valuation but only under particular
   conditions. In line with a process account drawing on mental simulation
   of product use, product valuation increases only if (1) the product is
   associated (vs. not associated) with a given weather state, as the match
   of product and weather facilitates mental simulation, and (2) the
