   difficult for investors to gauge the value of such decisions in the
   short term; longitudinal analysis is necessary. Accordingly, the authors
   apply latent growth modeling to a data set of 270 international
   codevelopment alliances announced over an 18-year period. The results
   demonstrate that investors reward firms for their international
   codevelopment alliances in the short term but punish them in the long
