AB Using a novel approach with video-recordings of sales interactions, this
   study focuses on a dynamic analysis of salesperson effectiveness in
   handling customer queries. We conceptualize salesperson behaviors,
   namely, resolving, relating, and emoting, as separate elements of
   customer query handling and empirically identify the distinct verbal and
   nonverbal cues that salespeople use to display these behaviors during
   sales interactions. We draw from compensation effects in social
   cognition theory to propose that customers' perceptions of a
