   strategy to influence consumers' organic post-consumption satisfaction
   ratings of entertainment products rich in cultural content. Drawing upon
   a communication theory framework, we develop hypotheses concerning
   multiple interaction effects between culture and marketing strategies on
   consumers' product evaluations. We test these hypotheses by analyzing
   consumer reviews of 260 movies in 25 country markets. In support of our
   hypotheses, we find that the cultural congruence between the product and
