   unique because prior to, versus after, a product's release, (1)
   differing information is available, (2) differing mental processes
   occur, and (3) consumers' behaviors have differing effects on other
   consumers, affecting diffusion differently. A quantitative study using
   secondary data for 254 new products illustrates the performance of the
   theory-based conceptualization.
