   introduction, alliance formation, channel restructuring) or
   announcements made by other entities such as regulatory bodies (e.g.,
   FDA approval) or competitors (e.g., new market entry). The event study
   methodology was developed by finance researchers but has been widely
   adopted in other fields, including marketing. We review the manner in
