   failure rate of M&As, the common practice of Western/global companies of
   augmenting their brand portfolio through local acquisitions, and the
   sensitivity of emerging market consumers to foreign brands. The present
   study is an initial attempt to understand the loyalty of consumers
   toward the acquired brands. Moreover, we investigate how such an
