   relationships. The authors develop a taxonomy of events, both internal
   and external to the relationship, that are proposed to create "defection
   energy," or the motivation to move a customer from relationship status
   quo toward a defection decision. The framework illustrates how these
   internal and external events interact with the organization's and the
   individual decision maker's goals, practices, and values to engage a
   dynamic anchoring and updating mechanism based on accumulated defection
