   customer's previous purchase ("recency") increases. As a result, firms
   face a "recency trap," whereby recency increases for customers who do
   not purchase in a given period, making it even less likely they will
   purchase in the next period. Eventually the customer is effectively lost
   to the firm. We develop and illustrate a modeling approach to target a
   firm's marketing efforts, keeping in mind the customer's recency state.
