   modeling. A recent simulation study recommends that, in most cases, this
   analysis is preferable to structural equation modeling because it
   outperforms the latter when the model is misspecified. This article
   examines the characteristics of generalized structured component
   analysis and reveals that the surprising previous findings are
   attributable to an incomplete experimental design and an error incurred
   during the software implementation of generalized structured component
   analysis. Simulated data show that generalized structured component
   analysis provides inconsistent estimates. In some instances, model
   misspecification can nearly neutralize this inconsistency, but in others
   it will reinforce the inconsistency. Moreover, generalized structured
